---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="Home">
    <div class="home-container">
        <h1><span class="prompt">~/</span> Hello World!</h1>
        <pre>
        printf("Hello, World!");
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
        println("Hello, World!");
        </pre>

        <div class="terminal-ascii-art">
<pre>
██████╗ ███╗   ██╗██████╗ ███████╗   ██╗███╗   ██╗
██╔══██╗████╗  ██║██╔══██╗██╔════╝   ██║████╗  ██║
██████╔╝██╔██╗ ██║██████╔╝█████╗     ██║██╔██╗ ██║
██╔═══╝ ██║╚██╗██║██╔══██╗██╔══╝     ██║██║╚██╗██║
██║     ██║ ╚████║██████╔╝███████╗██╗██║██║ ╚████
                          A_TERMINAL@PNBE (800001)
</pre>
        </div>

        <p>
            Hi, my name is Prashant and I am a backend developer <code>Java</code> developer. Over the years, I have
            developed applications that have run on desktops and web.
        </p>

        <div class="feature-block">
            <h2><span class="prompt">$</span> Why terminal</h2>
            <p>
                Why not! I had always wanted to do something like this. Terminals are interesting and fun. And you dont
                need a mouse. This personal project aims to show case the versatility of a terminal but currently it is
                far from there. I am working on it bit by bit.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="terminal-block">
            <h2><span class="prompt">$</span> Terminal Commands</h2>
            <p>Try these commands in the terminal:</p>
            <div class="code-block">
<pre>
help           # Show available commands
ls             # List available pages
cd /about      # Navigate to About page
cat /projects  # Preview Projects page

# You can see latest blogs using
cd blog
# You can open a blog based on the blog ID using the following command
view-post [id]

Have fun. I hope you enjoy your stay!
</pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</MainLayout>

<style>
    .home-container {
        max-width: 800px;
    }

    .prompt {
        color: var(--ctp-green);
        font-weight: bold;
    }

    .terminal-ascii-art {
        margin: 2rem 0;
        overflow-x: auto;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        color: var(--ctp-mauve);
    }

    .feature-block, .terminal-block {
        margin: 2rem 0;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 5px;
        background-color: var(--ctp-surface0);
    }

    .code-block {
        background-color: var(--ctp-crust);
        border-radius: 5px;
        padding: 1rem;
        overflow-x: auto;
        margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .code-block pre {
        margin: 0;
    }

    ul {
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
</style>